Product Description

Manage your home, even from a distance

Set schedules to automatically power your home electronics and appliances on or off at any time

  • New upgraded version, super mini size, doesn't take up much space, convenient to carry.
  • Works with Amazon Alexa Echo and Google Voice Control, making controlling your home truly easy.

Timing Switch

  • Ability to set schedules to automatically power on or off your home electronics and appliances at any time.
  • Able to limit your children's computer time with timer function.

Download the App!

  • No Amazon Alexa Echo? No Problem! This smart plug will work with your smartphone.
  • Just download the FREE APP and you can control your devices on APP.

Product Specifications

  • Weight: 4.9 ounces
  • Rated Voltage: 100 - 240V
  • Rated Current: 10A (Max.)
  • AC Frequency: 50-60 Hz Max.
  • Power: 2200W for 220V, 1100W for 110V
  • Wireless standard: Wi-Fi 2.4GHz b/g/n

  • No matter what electrical appliance is connected to, one smartphone can give complete control.
  • Plug a device into the Smart Plug, then follow our detailed instructions, and connect to your Wi-Fi network.
  • Remotely turn appliances and electronics on or off anywhere, anytime. At home or on the go, use Wi-Fi and mobile Networks to operate your devices.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • Richard Skelton
      4.0 out of 5 stars Favorite smart plug thus far
      Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2023
      Number of Items: 6Verified Purchase
      I have tried four or five smart plugs, and this is my favorite thus far. I do wish it only blocked one socket, which is why I give this 4 out of 5 stars. I have had relatively little issues with these plugs, and one held up outside during the polar vortex (we reached -50F windchill, and -16F actual lows, with only a few inches of snow, mostly ice) on my front porch (mostly covered, but open to the air and drifting snow) to work with my porch nutcracker. Other smart plugs have had issues being setup on my network, and this is the only one I haven't had issues. Even when swapping networks, it was relatively easy. I did brick one after giving it its 4th network to connect to in 2 months (I had some issues with a tech guy and had to swap all my passwords and SSIDs). So overall very happy with them, just wish they only blocked one socket though.
